	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Doogie wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Wouldn't it be simpler to import the SMB1 levels into the SMB2 (J) rom? I mean you just need to hack the titlescreen to be identical to SMB1 and export/import the levels from SMB1.</div>
<br />No, that would be insanely more difficult.  SMB1 and SMB2/Doki Doki Panic use completely different engines, with different memory layouts, graphics, mappers, etc.  In fact, it would be easier just to hack the ROM and change the layout of the stages manually to resemble those of SMB1.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
